i\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-30T16:41:41.000Z","msg":"單一世界撚已經收晒皮<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"dce67d210d0a182bc88e3480d598e44758d0f85a","tid":1132943,"uid":34123,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-30T16:43:09.000Z","msg":"The Russos confirm &mdash; Bucky knew. When Cap was preparing to for the trip, which is only supposed to last a few seconds in the main timeline, his old friend from Brooklyn gives him a surprisingly heavy farewell.<br />\n<br />\nSomehow, he was aware that Cap was going to live in the past, and it&rsquo;s probably more than just intuition. &ldquo;Especially when he says goodbye,&rdquo; Joe explained. &ldquo;He says, &lsquo;I&rsquo;ll miss you.&rsquo; Clearly he knows something.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nBut how? Has Winter Soldier already met with Old Cap at some previous point? It seems the answer is yes.<br />\n<br />\nOn the other hand, Joe adds, &ldquo;Sam doesn&rsquo;t know something.&rdquo; Falcon has no idea about Old Cap, which is why The Winter Soldier urges him to go up and talk to the now-elderly Steve Rogers. Bucky already has the answer to the questions Sam is going to ask.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n所以Bucky先推Sam過去<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n佢一早已經知<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2bbfcd2d71115c80104731cede18fd76ceaa4401","tid":1132943,"uid":34123,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-30T16:46:28.000Z","msg":"&ldquo;Obviously, if it doesn&rsquo;t work perfectly, it can undermine the emotional intention of the scene,&rdquo; says Anthony Russo. &ldquo;We did a lot of practical effects, so it was a very elaborate makeup job that was then augmented with CG, because there&rsquo;s certain things that you can&rsquo;t do with makeup in order to make Cap credibly that age.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nOld Cap大部分靠化妝再用CG執細節位"},{"pid":"a1821fd33e5d15bf71a707aba208a2300dedf0e6","tid":1132943,"uid":47905,"like":0,"dislike":6,"score":-6,"quote":{"pid":"7920c0906dff0a21d544608efcbc81cf8c2d98f6","tid":1132943,"uid":34123,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"3f0e06c7d5f7bfabbcb8ad41f400e672c7e8048d","tid":1132943,"uid":47905,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"6f41667c55d51405a5ff5e250ab0347d53e73d8c","tid":1132943,"uid":34123,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-04-30T16:29:06.000Z","msg":"So, has Cap&nbsp;been living in the past this whole time&nbsp;&mdash; or did he go and live in another dimension?<br />\n<br />\nThe directors say it&rsquo;s the latter.<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">&ldquo;If Cap were to go back into the past and live there, he would create a branched reality,&rdquo; Joe explained. &ldquo;The question then becomes, how is he back in&nbsp;this&nbsp;reality to give the shield away?&rdquo;</span><br />\n<br />\nThe brothers smile.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Interesting question, right?&rdquo; Joe said. &ldquo;Maybe there&rsquo;s a story there. There&rsquo;s a lot of layers built into this movie and we spent three years thinking through it, so it&rsquo;s fun to talk about it and hopefully fill in holes for people so they understand what we&rsquo;re thinking.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nThere are other questions in this sequence that set up this future story&hellip;"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-04-30T16:30:36.000Z","msg":"美國隊長 將會再次回歸<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/so